    scripture: "And they that be wise shall shine as the brightness of the firmament; and they that turn many to righteousness as the stars for ever and ever.",
    walk: `Friend, here is a glorious promise about the eternal destiny of those who shine for God: *they that be wise shall shine as the brightness of the firmament; and they that turn many to righteousness as the stars for ever and ever.* Those who live wisely as the light, and who turn others to righteousness, will shine like the stars forever. The shining life is not only for this present world; it has an eternal dimension, a glory that will blaze forth forever in the world to come.

Consider the promise: *they that be wise shall shine as the brightness of the firmament.* Those who are wise, who live the wise and shining life we have been exploring, will one day shine like the brightness of the heavens, like the radiance of the sky itself. There is coming a day when those who shone for God in this dark world will shine with a far greater brightness, radiant with glory, gleaming like the firmament. The dim and often unnoticed shining of the faithful in this life will give way to a brilliant, glorious shining in the life to come. The light we bear now is but a foretaste of the glory we will shine with then.

And see the special promise for those who lead others to Christ: *they that turn many to righteousness as the stars for ever and ever.* Those who turn many to righteousness, who lead others out of darkness into the light of Christ, will shine like the stars forever and ever. There is a special and eternal glory reserved for those who win others to the Lord, who hold forth the word of life and see others come to righteousness through them. They will shine like stars, brilliant and enduring, forever and ever. This is a powerful encouragement, friend, to give ourselves to leading others to Christ, for those who turn many to righteousness will shine with a special and eternal radiance.

Notice the eternal scope: *for ever and ever.* This shining is not temporary, not fading, but everlasting. The faithful who shone for God in this passing world will shine forever in the world to come, their glory never dimming, never fading, enduring for ever and ever. What a contrast to the fleeting glories of this world, which fade so quickly. The glory of those who shine for God is eternal, an everlasting radiance that will blaze on forever. This eternal perspective transforms our present shining, giving it a weight and significance that reaches into eternity.

So let this eternal promise inspire your shining, friend. The shining life you are called to is not only for this present world; it has an eternal dimension. Those who live wisely as the light, and who turn others to righteousness, will shine like the stars forever and ever. So do not grow weary in shining, even when your light seems small and unnoticed in this dark world. A day is coming when the faithful will shine with the brightness of the heavens, and those who led others to Christ will shine like stars forever. Give yourself, then, to the wise and shining life, and especially to turning others to righteousness, that you might shine, not only now, but for ever and ever, to the glory of God. The shining of the faithful is eternal, friend, so shine.`,
    prayer: `Lord, thank You for the glorious promise that those who live wisely as the light, and who turn others to righteousness, will shine like the stars forever and ever. When my light seems small and unnoticed in this dark world, lift my eyes to that eternal glory. Help me not to grow weary in shining, and stir me to give myself to turning others to righteousness, that I might shine, not only now, but forever, to Your glory. In the name of Jesus Christ. Amen.`,
    oneThing: `Today, let the eternal promise that "they that be wise shall shine... for ever and ever" inspire your shining. Give yourself especially to "turning others to righteousness," investing in leading one person toward Christ.`,
